# Content Pack Rules

## Never mutate an existing pack's content

A child's mastery percentage is calculated as `problems practiced / total problems in pack`.
Adding items to an existing pack dilutes the percentage — a child who was at 100% drops to 60%
and feels cheated out of earned progress.

**ALWAYS create a new pack when adding new content. NEVER add items to an existing pack.**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — dilutes existing progress
await prisma.mathProblem.createMany({
  data: newProblems.map(p => ({ ...p, packId: 'math_add_singles' })) // existing pack!
})

// ✅ GOOD — new content gets its own pack
await prisma.pack.create({ data: { id: 'math_add_singles_v2', subject: 'math', ... } })
await prisma.mathProblem.createMany({
  data: newProblems.map(p => ({ ...p, packId: 'math_add_singles_v2' }))
})
```

This rule applies to ALL content types: `Word` (Chinese), `MathProblem`, and any future subject tables.

## Deleting or replacing packs

Deleting a pack is fine when replacing the entire topic set (e.g., a full seed reset).
Always delete child records first to respect FK constraints:
1. `MathProgress` / `ChineseProgress`
2. `AnswerEvent` (where `packId` matches)
3. `MathProblem` / `Word`
4. `Pack`
